  "response": "In September 2016, India conducted surgical strikes across the Line of Control (LoC) in Pakistan-occupied Kashmir (PoK) in response to the Uri terror attack. Here's a summary of global reactions and Pakistan's response:\n\nGlobal Reactions:\n1. United States: Supported India's right to self-defense\n2. Russia: Urged restraint and peaceful dialogue\n3. China: Called for peaceful resolution\n4. United Kingdom: Recommended dialogue between India and Pakistan\n5. Most Western countries viewed the strike as a justified response to terrorism\n\nPakistan's Reaction:\n1. Strongly denied any surgical strikes occurred\n2. Claimed Indian forces did not cross the LoC\n3. Condemned the action as a violation of international boundaries\n4. Raised diplomatic protests\n5. Warned of potential escalation\n6. Approached international forums to highlight the issue\n\nAt the United Nations:\n1. Pakistan attempted to internationalize the issue\n2. Sought condemnation of India's actions\n3. Called for mediation\n\nThe surgical strike was widely seen as a significant military and diplomatic response by India to cross-border terrorism, demonstrating a more proactive approach to national security.",
